videos.name: Catalyst: Out of Africa
videos.description: Prof Vanessa Hayes is searching for the origins of modern society, revealing the bedrock of human genetic diversity. Her work exposes some startling truths about racial inequality in modern medicine.

videos.name: The Diet Myth
videos.description: The Diet Myth reveals cutting edge research that turns conventional medical wisdom on its head. We have always thought of bacteria as our enemy - but now we know some bacteria are our allies.

videos.name: Insight: Placebo
videos.description: Is everything just in our mind? Insight asks how strong is the placebo effect, and how can we best utilise it?

videos.name: Afghanistan: Inside Australia's War
videos.description: In their own words & using never-before-seen helmet-cam battle footage, Australian fighting men & women reveal their war. In the wake of 9/11 a Special Forces war builds to a fateful battle.

videos.name: Behind the News: 1/03/2016
videos.description: This week's stories: Voting Changes: Federal Government announces changes to how the Senate is elected; Syria Ceasefire; Endeavour Tour; Space Program; Penguin Protection Dogs: Middle Island Victoria

videos.name: The Valley of the Kings: Death, Burial and the Afterlife
videos.description: Egyptologist Dr Joann Fletcher reveals a strange and mysterious world: the ancient Egyptian afterlife.

videos.name: Opera Stories: Arabella
videos.description: Some of the greatest stars of the opera world: Renee Fleming, Elina Garanca, Roberta Alagna and Beatrice Uria-Monzon are our guides exploring four major operas.

videos.name: Full Proof: Magnets
videos.description: Isabel lives on a barge, where they still have an old compass. Isabel experiments with magnets.

videos.name: Jila: Painted Waters Of The Great Sandy
videos.description: The Ngurrara people know their desert country but to claim their Native Title they need to show knowledge and ownership of the land.  They decide to paint their country on a massive scale.

videos.name: Gayby Baby
videos.description: Gayby Baby is a portrait of four kids - Gus, Ebony, Matt and Graham - whose parents all happen to be gay. In this heartfelt documentary, we get to know the four kids and learn their views.

videos.name: Exploration India
videos.description: Three 13 year olds are going on a trip of a lifetime - to discover the geography of India. The teenagers find out what life is really like for the people of India.

videos.name: Talking Language: Gunditjmara
videos.description: Talking Language with Ernie Dingo is a personal journey providing a unique understanding of how knowledge of Aboriginal languages is shaped by ancestral connections to the land, stars, water and sea.

videos.name: Stephen Hawking's Future Universe: Episode 2 - Code Red
videos.description: Dealing with crises has always been one of science's huge challenges. Stephen Hawking investigates astonishing breakthroughs that are making human life less fragile.

videos.name: Absolute Genius With Dick and Dom: Fox Talbot
videos.description: From Archimedes to Faraday, Dick and Dom explore the work of the most important inventors and scientists in history.

videos.name: Changing Minds: The Inside Story - Episode 2
videos.description: Jeffrey was brought to Liverpool Hospital by police after an altercation. He thought he'd be there for a few hours. A month later he's fighting for his freedom, but is he well enough to be released?

videos.name: Changing Minds: The Inside Story - Episode 1
videos.description: We go inside the locked wards of Liverpool Hospital's Mental Health Unit and meet Patrick the high flying IT specialist who was admitted after hitching a ride on the bull bar of a truck.

videos.name: The Valley Of The Kings: Life
videos.description: Life - Dr Joann Fletcher goes on a fascinating journey in search of ordinary people, not the great Pharaohs but the people who built and populated this incredible civilisation.

videos.name: Full Proof: Action Reaction
videos.description: Raynnan lives with his parents close to the rocket launching site of the European Space Centre in French Guiana. Raynnan experiments with action/reaction and builds his own rocket.

videos.name: We Are Young
videos.description: A reality show about two exchange students - one from China and one from Australia. They will live and study in their new surroundings for 30 days, learning about a new culture and way of life.

videos.name: Molly: The Real Thing
videos.description: Over 50 celebrities share stories about the man in the hat  Molly Meldrum. Join Kylie Minogue, Gene Simmons and more as they reveal outrageous insights into this Australian rock legend.

videos.name: Four Corners: Guns in the USA
videos.description: Exploring America's gun culture where kids learn to shoot and their classrooms are designed to be bulletproof. How America grapples with gun violence.

videos.name: New Secrets of the Terracotta Warriors
videos.description: With exclusive access to pioneering research conducted by University College London and the Terracotta Army Museum, this documentary uncovers new secrets of China's fabled warriors.

videos.name: Hidden Histories: Forgotten Photos of WW1
videos.description: This is the story of the Great War as never before told - through the personal photographs of the men and women from both sides, from those on the front line to those on the home front.

videos.name: The Family Law: Episode 6 - Love Is in the Air
videos.description: Jenny and Danny's twentieth wedding anniversary looms before them, and in an unfortunate bit of timing, Candy and Wayne have also started their own wedding arrangements. (Final) #TheFamilyLawSBS

videos.name: The Family Law: Episode 5 - Everything's Coming Up Roses
videos.description: After Andrew moves out with Danny, a heartbroken and catatonic Jenny finds herself caught in the throes of a deep depression. As her illness becomes more severe, Benjamin tries to cheer his mother up by inviting her best - and possibly only - friend from Malaysia, the mysterious Aunty Rose. But when Rose reveals her true colours as a judgemental control freak, Benjamin has to summon his siblings to save Jenny.
